## Context
PR #649 split the tech rep structurally (corpus + analysis) and assessed
the companion paper's three fatal problems. The analysis report is now a
pipeline walkthrough with no "why." The companion paper has useful prose
that should feed back in before the companion paper is retired.

## Actions
1. Section 2 (lit review) → introduction to the analysis report, motivating
   the methods choices (why embeddings, why sliding-window divergence, why
   not LDA/STM/BERTopic)
2. Section 6.1 (comparison with topic models) → discussion section at the
   end of the analysis report
3. Section 6.4 (limitations) → add to analysis report (currently missing)
4. Section 5.1 honesty correction → acknowledge mid-2010s JS divergence
   signal, reframe from "no Paris break" to "Copenhagen was the dominant
   founding shift, mid-2010s saw real redistribution"
5. Delete companion-paper.qmd and remove from _quarto.yml
6. Update architecture.md to reflect 3 documents not 4

## Test
Analysis report builds with `make output/content/technical-report.pdf`.
No broken cross-references. Companion paper removed from render list.

## Exit criteria
Companion paper retired. Analysis report has introduction, discussion,
limitations, and honest section 5.1. The analysis report reads as a
self-contained technical document, not a pipeline walkthrough.
